{"id":"9512","name":"Add to Cookbook - Nextcloud Cookbook","tagline":"Shortcut to automatically import new recipes via share menu to your Nextcloud Cookbook","icon":"ios14 c4274264319 g61442","latest":"28365","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<h1>What is it about</h1>\n<p>This shortcut makes adding recipes to your <a href=\"https://apps.nextcloud.com/apps/cookbook\">Nextcloud Cookbook</a> really convenient.</p>\n<h2>Add new Recipe</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Open URL with desired Recipe</li>\n<li>Open share menu</li>\n<li>Press Shortcut \"Add to Cookbook\"</li>\n<li>Done</li>\n</ol>\n<p>This also works from apps that share more than the actual URL:\n<em>\"Try this new recipe: https://url.me\"</em></p>\n<h2>Configuration</h2>\n<p>When adding the Shortcut it prompts you to enter:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>URL of your Nextcloud instance</li>\n<li>Your username</li>\n<li>An AppPassword</li>\n</ol>\n<p>DO NOT USE YOUR ACTUAL PASSWORD</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.nextcloud.com/server/stable/user_manual/en/session_management.html?highlight=password#managing-devices\">Rather create an app password</a>:\nGo to your Nextcloud settings &gt; Security and create a new app password.\nIt should look like this: xxxxx-xxxxx-xxxxx-xxxxx-xxxxx</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>0.1.2 - June 23, 2021, 5:42 p.m.</strong></p><p>- new glyphe and color<br>- now actually present in share menu</p>"}